        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 220°C fan. Line a baking tray with baking paper.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub in the butter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Put the {{self-raising-flour}}, {{baking-powder}}, {{fine-sea-salt}}, and {{mustard-powder}} in a large bowl. Add the cold {{unsalted-butter}} and rub it in with your fingertips until the mixture looks like rough breadcrumbs. Work quickly so the butter stays cold. Add 100 g of the grated {{mature-cheddar}} and toss it through the crumbs.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add the milk",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour in the cold {{whole-milk}} and mix quickly with a palette knife until a ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "shaggy dough",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpaefc8v0000mov44jalkedr"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " forms. Do not knead or squeeze. If the dough looks too dry, add another tablespoon of milk.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pat, cut, and top",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Turn the dough onto a floured surface and pat it to 2.5 cm thick. Cut rounds with a 5 cm cutter, pressing straight down without twisting. Arrange on the tray, brush the tops with a little milk, and scatter over the remaining 40 g of grated cheese.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 12 to 15 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 12 to 15 minutes until the tops are deep golden and the cheese is bubbling and browned in patches. The scones should have risen with a slight crack around the equator. Eat warm, split with butter.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
